    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1931-10-09T18:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1931-10-09T18:00:00-05:00" n="617"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d617">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">724.3415/1416: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Argentina</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Bliss</hi>
                    </persName>)<note n="88" xml:id="d617fn88">The same, <hi rend="italic">mutatis
                            mutandis</hi>, on the same date, to the Ambassadors in Chile (No. 47)
                        and Peru (No. 55).</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-10-09T18:00:00-05:00"
                            >October 9, 1931—6 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>69. Following strictly confidential telegram 70, October 9, noon, received from
                    Embassy Rio.</p>
                <p>[Here follows the text of the telegram printed <hi rend="italic">supra.</hi>]</p>
                <p>Department has replied today as follows:</p>
                <p>[Here follows the text of telegram No. 70, October 9, 7 p.m., printed on <ref
                        target="#pg_759">page 759</ref>.]</p>
                <p>Please take the matter up with Minister for Foreign Affairs in the sense of
                    instructions to the Ambassador at Rio.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Stimson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
